          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong></strong></p> <p> <p> <b>Confidential Informant Accountability Act of 2017</b> <p>This bill directs the Department of Justice, the Department of Homeland Security, and the Department of the Treasury to report to Congress on: (1) serious crimes committed by informants maintained by their law enforcement agencies, (2) amounts paid to the informants, and (3) amounts received through information from or cooperation by the informants. <p>The bill defines the term &quot;serious crime.&quot;]]></text>
